#. +> trunk5
#: ../../<rst_epilog>:1
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_fish-eye_2_02.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_fish-eye_2_02.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_fish-eye_2_02.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:12
msgid "Painting Assistants"
msgstr "お絵描きアシスト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:17
msgid "Painting with Assistants"
msgstr "お絵描きアシスト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:19
msgid ""
"The assistant system allows you to have a little help while drawing straight "
"lines or circles."
msgstr "直線や円を描く補助をするアシストの仕組みです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:21
msgid ""
"They can function as a preview shape, or you can snap onto them with the "
"freehand brush tool. In the tool options of free hand brush, you can "
"toggle :guilabel:`Snap to Assistants` to turn on snapping."
msgstr ""
"目安の形としても、フリーハンドブラシでスナップするところとしても機能します。"
"フリーハンドブラシのツールオプションで :guilabel:`補助線にスナップ` をオンに"
"することでスナップできます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:27
msgid "Krita's vanishing point assistants in action."
msgstr "Krita の消失点アシストを使ってみたところ。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:27
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_oblique.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Krita_basic_assistants.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_oblique.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:29
msgid "The following assistants are available in Krita:"
msgstr "次の補助ツールが Krita で使えます:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:32
msgid "Types"
msgstr "種類"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:34
msgid ""
"There are several types in Krita. You can select a type of assistant via the "
"tool options docker."
msgstr ""
"いくつかのタイプが Krita にはあります。ツールのオプションドッカーからアシスト"
"のタイプを選択できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:39
msgid "Ellipse"
msgstr "楕円"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:41
msgid "An assistant for drawing ellipses and circles."
msgstr "楕円や円を描くアシストです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:43
msgid ""
"This assistant consists of three points: the first two are the axis of the "
"ellipse, and the last one is to determine its width."
msgstr ""
"このアシストは3つの点で成り立っています: 最初の二つが楕円の軸で、残りの一つが"
"幅を決めます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:46
msgid "Concentric Ellipse"
msgstr "同心円"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:46
msgid ""
"The same an ellipse, but allows for making ellipses that are concentric to "
"each other."
msgstr "楕円と同じですが、同心状に円を作ることができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:48
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:146
msgid ""
"If you press the :kbd:`Shift` key while holding the first two handles, they "
"will snap to perfectly horizontal or vertical lines. Press the :kbd:`Shift` "
"key while holding the third handle, and it'll snap to a perfect circle."
msgstr ""
"最初の二つのハンドルを掴みながら :kbd:`Shift` キーを押すと、水平や垂直線上に"
"スナップします。3つ目のハンドルを掴みながら :kbd:`Shift` を押すと正円にスナッ"
"プします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:56
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Perspective"
msgid "Perspective Ellipse"
msgstr "パース"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:58
msgid ""
"Alternative assistant for drawing ellipses. It can be used either simply, to "
"draw an ellipse defined by a tetragon which the ellipse is tangential to, or "
"in a perspective as an ellipse representing the perspective transformation "
"of a circle."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:62
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_1_point_perspective.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_ellipse_in_perspective.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_1_point_perspective.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:63
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "This assistant consists of three points: the first two are the axis of "
#| "the ellipse, and the last one is to determine its width."
msgid ""
"The assistant consists of four points, which are the corners for the "
"tetragon defining the ellipse."
msgstr ""
"このアシストは3つの点で成り立っています: 最初の二つが楕円の軸で、残りの一つが"
"幅を決めます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:65
msgid ""
"The X-like marks show the locations of the vanishing points for the "
"perspective."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:67
msgid ""
"There are two sets of lines inside the ellipse: one, solid, are the lines "
"connecting points where the ellipse touches the tetragon. They are the axis "
"of the circle in perspective. The dotted lines represent the current, actual "
"axis of the final ellipse."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:72
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:199
msgid "Perspective"
msgstr "パース"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:74
msgid ""
"This ruler allows you to draw and manipulate grids on the canvas that can "
"serve as perspective guides for your painting. A grid can be added to your "
"canvas by first clicking the tool in the toolbar and then clicking four "
"points on the canvas which will serve as the four corners of your grid."
msgstr ""
"このルーラーによって、お絵描きの際の透視ガイドの役割を持つキャンバス上のグ"
"リッドを描いたり操ることができます。グリッドはまずツールバーのツールをクリッ"
"クし、そしてグリッドの 4 つの角となるグリッド状の点をクリックすることで追加で"
"きます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:77
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/tools/Perspectivegrid.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Perspectivegrid.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/tools/Perspectivegrid.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:78
msgid ""
"This grid can be used with the 'perspective' sensor, which can influence "
"brushes."
msgstr ""
"このグリッドはブラシに影響する'パース'センサーとして使うことができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:80
msgid ""
"The grid can be manipulated by pulling on any of its four corners. The grid "
"can be extended by clicking and dragging a midpoint of one of its edges. "
"This will allow you to expand the grid at other angles. This process can be "
"repeated on any subsequent grid or grid section."
msgstr ""
"グリッドは 4 つの角のどれかを引っ張ることで操作することができます。グリッドは"
"どれか一辺の中点をクリックアンドドラッグすることで引き伸ばすことができます。"
"これによって他の角のグリッドを広げることができます。このプロセスは、生成され"
"たいかなるグリッドやグリッドセクションに対しても繰り返し行うことができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:82
msgid ""
"If you press the :kbd:`Shift` key while holding any of the corner handles, "
"they'll snap to one of the other corner handles, in sets. You can delete any "
"grid by clicking on the cancel button at its center. This tool can be used "
"to build reference for complex scenes."
msgstr ""
"どのコーナーハンドルを掴んでいるときでも、:kbd:`Shift` キーを押すことで他の"
"コーナーハンドルにスナップします。また、真ん中にあるボタンをクリックすること"
"でグリッドを削除することができます。このツールは複雑な風景を描く際の参考とし"
"て使うことができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:87
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:91
msgid "Ruler"
msgstr "定規"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:89
msgid "There are three assistants in this group:"
msgstr "このグループには3つのアシストがあります:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:92
msgid "Helps create a straight line between two points."
msgstr "2点の間に直線を作る。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:93
msgid "Infinite Ruler"
msgstr "無限定規"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:94
msgid ""
"Extrapolates a straight line beyond the two visible points on the canvas."
msgstr "キャンバス上の2点を超えた直線を推測します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:96
msgid "Parallel Ruler"
msgstr "平行定規"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:96
msgid ""
"This ruler allows you to draw a line parallel to the line between the two "
"points anywhere on the canvas."
msgstr "この定規で2点に平行な線をキャンバス上のどこでも描くことができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:98
msgid ""
"If you press the :kbd:`Shift` key while holding the first two handles, they "
"will snap to perfectly horizontal or vertical lines."
msgstr ""
"最初の二つのハンドルを掴みながら :kbd:`Shift` キーを押すと、水平や垂直線上に"
"スナップします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:102
msgid ""
"Of these, the :guilabel:`Ruler` assistant also has extra options to add "
"markers:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:104
msgid "Subdivisions"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:105
msgid ""
"This adds notches to the length of the assistant, evenly spread over the "
"assistant."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:106
msgid "Minor Subdivisions"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:107
msgid "This adds extra smaller notches between the :guilabel:`Subdivisions`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:112
msgid "Spline"
msgstr "スプライン"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:114
msgid ""
"This assistant allows you to position and adjust four points to create a "
"cubic bézier curve. You can then draw along the curve, snapping your brush "
"stroke directly to the curve line. Perfect curves every time!"
msgstr ""
"4点から三次ベジェ曲線を作るアシストです。カーブに沿って描くことができ、曲線に"
"直接ブラシストロークをスナップします。これでいつでも完璧なカーブが描けます！"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:116
msgid ""
"If you press the :kbd:`Shift` key while holding the first two handles, they "
"will snap to perfectly horizontal or vertical lines. Press the :kbd:`Shift` "
"key while holding the third or fourth handle, they will snap relative to the "
"handle they are attached to."
msgstr ""
"最初の二つのハンドルを掴みながら :kbd:`Shift` キーを押すと、水平や垂直線上に"
"スナップします。3つ目や4つ目のハンドルを掴みながら :kbd:`Shift` キーを押す"
"と、近いハンドルにスナップします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:121
msgid "Vanishing Point"
msgstr "消失点"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:123
msgid ""
"This assistant allows you to create a vanishing point, typically used for a "
"horizon line. A preview line is drawn and all your snapped lines are drawn "
"to this line."
msgstr ""
"地平線によく使われる、消失点を作るアシストです。目安の線が引かれこの線に沿っ"
"て描く線がスナップします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:125
msgid ""
"It is one point, with four helper points to align it to previously created "
"perspective lines."
msgstr "1点と4つの補助点に沿わせて消失点が作られます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:127
msgid "They are made and manipulated with the :ref:`assistant_tool`."
msgstr ":ref:`assistant_tool` と一緒に作られ操作します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:129
msgid ""
"If you press the :kbd:`Shift` key while holding the center handle, they will "
"snap to perfectly horizontal or vertical lines depending on the position of "
"where it previously was."
msgstr ""
"中央のハンドルを掴みながら :kbd:`Shift` キーを押すと、それまであった場所に基"
"づいて水平や垂直線上にスナップします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:133
msgid "The vanishing point assistant also shows several general lines."
msgstr "消失点アシストはまた複数の線が表示されます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:135
msgid ""
"When you've just created, or when you've just moved a vanishing point "
"assistant, it will be selected. This means you can modify the amount of "
"lines shown in the tool options of the :ref:`assistant_tool`."
msgstr ""
"作ったばっかりや、消失点アシストを動かしたばかりの状態では選択されています。"
"つまり :ref:`assistant_tool` のツールオプションで表示される線の量を編集する事"
"ができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:140
msgid "Fish Eye Point"
msgstr "魚眼レンズ視点"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:142
msgid ""
"Like the vanishing point assistant, this assistant is per a set of parallel "
"lines in a 3d space. So to use it effectively, use two, where the second is "
"at a 90 degrees angle of the first, and add a vanishing point to the center "
"of both. Or combine one with a parallel ruler and a vanishing point, or even "
"one with two vanishing points. The possibilities are quite large."
msgstr ""
"消失点アシストのように、このアシストは三次元空間の平行線ごとに設定します。効"
"果的に使うには二つ使い、二つ目を一つ目から90度の角度にし、両方の中心に消失点"
"を追加します。または平行定規と消失点を組み合わせるか、消失点を二つ使っても良"
"いでしょう。可能性はとても大きいです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:144
msgid ""
"This assistant will not just give feedback/snapping between the vanishing "
"points, but also give feedback to the relative left and right of the "
"assistant. This is so you can use it in edge-cases like panoramas with "
"relative ease."
msgstr ""
"このアシストは消失点間で操作/スナップするだけでなく、アシストの左右関係をも感"
"じさせてくれます。パノラマのような極端な場合でも簡単に使うことができます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:151
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:248
msgid "2 Point Perspective"
msgstr "二点透視図法"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:155
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "This assistant simplifies the setup of a two point perspective by putting "
#| "the two vanishing points and the parallel vertical ruler into one single "
#| "assistant. This allows it to draw a grid of squares. It requires 3 points "
#| "at minimum: 2 for perspective, and the final for the mid-point of the "
#| "vanishing points, which controls how the grid is drawn."
msgid ""
"This assistant simplifies the setup of a two point perspective by combining "
"the functions of the :ref:`assistant_vanishing_point` assistant and the "
"parallel vertical :ref:`assistant_ruler` into one single assistant. "
"Additionally, it displays accurate square grid planes of the configured "
"perspective, which can help you visually tune the intensity of the "
"perspective distortion."
msgstr ""
"このアシストは二点透視図法のセットアップを、2つの消失点と平行な垂直の目盛を一"
"つのアシストにまとめることで単純化しています。これによって正方形のグリッドを"
"描けるようにしています。これには少なくとも3点必要です: 2つの消失点と、その中"
"点です。中点はグリッドをどのように描くかをコントロールします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:157
msgid ""
"It requires 3 points to achieve this: the first 2 of which are the vanishing "
"points, while the third point is used to determine the *center of vision*, "
"which affects how the grid is displayed. In two point perspective the "
"*center of vision* is a point on the horizon line, so the assistant displays "
"a small notch to indicate its location. Generally, the center of vision is "
"also where the main focus of an illustration is."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:159
msgid "Density"
msgstr "密度"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:160
msgid ""
"An extra option in the tool options, this controls how dense the grid is."
msgstr ""
"ツールオプションにある追加のオプションです。これはグリッドの密度を指定しま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:162
msgid "Enable Vertical Ruler"
msgstr "垂直方向の目盛を有効化"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:162
msgid ""
"This allows you to disable the vertical ruler, so that the assistant is only "
"two vanishing points and a grid."
msgstr ""
"これによって垂直方向の目盛を無効にすることができます。そうするとこのアシスト"
"は 2 つの消失点とグリッドのみを表示します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:166
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_2_pointperspective_03.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_2_pointperspective_03.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_2_pointperspective_03.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:166
msgid ""
"In the above image, a two point perspective with an area limiter is enough "
"to draw an indoor area. The assistant is colored blue here."
msgstr ""
"上の画像では、室内の空間を描くのに範囲に制限をつけた 2 つのパースで十分です。"
"ここではアシストは青で色付けられています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:171
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Linear Perspective"
msgid "Curvilinear Perspective"
msgstr "線遠近法"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:175
msgid ""
"Using this assistant, one can draw parallel lines that curve to converge at "
"two specified vanishing points. This assistant is similar to "
"the :ref:`assistant_fish_eye` assistant, except that it uses circular arcs "
"to create curvature instead of ellipses. This allows for a different type of "
"curved perspective compared to the :ref:`assistant_fish_eye`, especially "
"whenever it comes to drawing outside of the vanishing points."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:178
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_1_point_perspective.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/CurvilinearPerspective.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_1_point_perspective.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:179
msgid ""
"The assistant can be used to create 4-point, 5-point, and certain forms of 6-"
"point perspectives through utilizing combinations of this assistant and "
"other assistants, such as :ref:`assistant_vanishing_point`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:182
msgid "Tips"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:184
msgid ""
"You can hold specific key combinations while moving a vanishing point to "
"activate the following behaviours:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:186
msgid ":kbd:`Alt`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:187
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "The vanishing point assistant also shows several general lines."
msgid "The vanishing point will only move along the horizon line"
msgstr "消失点アシストはまた複数の線が表示されます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:188
msgid ":kbd:`Ctrl`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:189
msgid ""
"The grid will rotate along with the vanishing point on the horizon line. "
"This allows you to easily draw several two-point objects that belong in the "
"same scene at various angles to each other."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:191
msgid ":kbd:`Ctrl+Shift`"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:191
msgid ""
"Both vanishing points move to change the visual size of the grid's *field of "
"view*."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:194
msgid "Tutorials"
msgstr "チュートリアル"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:196
msgid ""
"Check out this in depth discussion and tutorial on https://www.youtube.com/"
"watch?v=OhEv2pw3EuI"
msgstr ""
"掘り下げたチュートリアルをここで見てみてください。https://www.youtube.com/"
"watch?v=OhEv2pw3EuI"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:199
msgid "Technical Drawing"
msgstr "製図"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:202
msgid "Setting up Krita for technical drawing-like perspectives"
msgstr "製図のようなパース用に Krita をセットアップする"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:204
msgid ""
"So now that you've seen the wide range of drawing assistants that Krita "
"offers, here is an example of how using these assistants you can set up "
"Krita for technical drawing."
msgstr ""
"ここまで Krita が提供する幅広いアシストを見てきました。技術的に描くために "
"Krita のアシストを使う例がこちらです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:206
msgid ""
"This tutorial below should give you an idea of how to set up the assistants "
"for specific types of technical views."
msgstr ""
"下のチュートリアルは技術的な視点で特定のタイプにアシストを設定するのに良いヒ"
"ントが得られるでしょう。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:208
msgid ""
"If you want to instead do the true projection, check out :ref:`the "
"projection category <cat_projection>`."
msgstr ""
"代わりに true projection をする場合は、:ref:`the projection category "
"<cat_projection>` を見てください。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:211
msgid "Orthographic"
msgstr "正射影"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:213
msgid ""
"Orthographic is a mode where you try to look at something from the left or "
"the front. Typically, you try to keep everything in exact scale with each "
"other, unlike perspective deformation."
msgstr ""
"正射影は何かを左や正面から見ようとするモードです。透視投影とは違い典型的には"
"すべてのものがそれぞれ同じサイズになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:215
msgid ""
"The key assistant you want to use here is the Parallel Ruler. You can set "
"these up horizontally or vertically, so you always have access to a Grid."
msgstr ""
"ここで鍵となるアシストは平行定規です。水平か垂直にセットし、常にグリッドにア"
"クセスできるようになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:218
msgid "Axonometric"
msgstr "軸測投影"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:220
msgid "All of these are set up using three Parallel Rulers."
msgstr "これらすべては3つの平行定規を使って作られました。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:223
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_oblique.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_oblique.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_oblique.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:225
msgid "Oblique"
msgstr "斜投影"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:225
msgid ""
"For oblique, set two parallel rulers to horizontal and vertical, and one to "
"an angle, representing depth."
msgstr ""
"斜投影には二つの平行定規を水平と垂直にセットし、一つに角度を付けて奥行きを表"
"現します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:228
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_dimetric.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_dimetric.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_dimetric.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:230
msgid "Dimetric & Isometric"
msgstr "等角投影と二等角投影"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:230
msgid ""
"Isometric perspective has technically all three rulers set up at 120° from "
"each other. Except when it's game isometric, then it's a type of dimetric "
"projection where the diagonal values are a 116.565° from the main. The "
"latter can be easily set up by snapping the assistants to a grid."
msgstr ""
"二等角投影は、技術的には 3 つのすべての定規が互いに 120° 離れています。ただし"
"ゲームにおける二等角投影は、斜めの定規が垂直になっている定規から 116.565° 離"
"れている等角投影となっています。後者に関してはアシストをグリッドにスナップす"
"ることでセットできます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:233
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_trimetric.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_trimetric.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_trimetric.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:235
msgid "Trimetric"
msgstr "斜方投影"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:235
msgid ""
"Is when all the angles are slightly different. Often looks like a slightly "
"angled isometric."
msgstr ""
"すべての角が少しずつ異なります。しばしば若干角度の付いた等角投影にも見えま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:238
msgid "Linear Perspective"
msgstr "線遠近法"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:241
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_1_point_perspective.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_1_point_perspective.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_1_point_perspective.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:243
msgid "1 Point Perspective"
msgstr "一点透視図法"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:243
msgid ""
"A 1 point perspective is set up using 1 vanishing point, and two crossing "
"perpendicular parallel rulers."
msgstr "1消失点を使った一点透視図法と、二つの交差する平行定規です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:246
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_2_point_perspective.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_2_point_perspective.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_2_point_perspective.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:248
msgid ""
"A 2 point perspective is set up using 2 vanishing point and 1 vertical "
"parallel ruler. Often, putting the vanishing points outside the frame a "
"little can decrease the strength of it. You can also use "
"a :ref:`assistant_2_point` Ruler to set this one up very quickly."
msgstr ""
"二点透視図法は2つの消失点と1つの垂直平行定規を使ってセットします。しばしば、"
"フレーム外に消失点を置くと強さが少し失われます。ま"
"た、:ref:`assistant_2_point` ルーラーを使うことで素早くセットアップすることも"
"できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:251
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_2_pointperspective_02.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_2_pointperspective_02.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_2_pointperspective_02.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:253
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_3_point_perspective.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_3_point_perspective.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_3_point_perspective.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:255
msgid "3 Point Perspective"
msgstr "三点透視図法"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:255
msgid "A 3 point perspective is set up using 3 vanishing point rulers."
msgstr "三点透視図法は3つの消失点を使ってセットします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:258
msgid "Logic of the vanishing point"
msgstr "消失点の理論"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:260
msgid ""
"There's a little secret that perspective tutorials don't always tell you, "
"and that's that a vanishing point is the point where any two parallel lines "
"meet. This means that a 1 point perspective and 2 point perspective are "
"virtually the same."
msgstr ""
"遠近法チュートリアルが必ずしも説明しない小さい秘密があり、それは消失点は二つ"
"の平行線が必ずぶつかる場所であるということです。つまり一点透視図法と二点透視"
"図法は仮想的には同じです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:262
msgid ""
"We can prove this via a little experiment. That good old problem: drawing a "
"rail-road."
msgstr ""
"少し実験して確かめてみましょう。古くからある良い問題: 線路を描くことです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:265
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_01.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_01.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_01.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:266
msgid ""
"You are probably familiar with the problem: How to determine where the next "
"beam is going to be, as perspective projection will make them look closer "
"together."
msgstr ""
"おそらくこの問題は身に覚えがあるでしょう: 透視投影で近くに見えてしまう、次の"
"枕木をどこに置けば良いのか。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:268
msgid ""
"Typically, the solution is to draw a line in the middle and then draw lines "
"diagonally across. After all, those lines are parallel, meaning that the "
"exact same distance is used."
msgstr ""
"典型的な答えは真ん中と対角線に線を引くことです。結局、これらの線は平行で、全"
"く同じ距離が使われています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:271
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_02.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_02.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_02.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:272
msgid ""
"But because they are parallel, we can use a vanishing point assistant "
"instead, and we use the alignment handles to align it to the diagonal of the "
"beam, and to the horizontal (here marked with red)."
msgstr ""
"しかし平行であることにより、代わりに消失点アシストを使って、調整ハンドルを枕"
"木の対角線上と、水平に沿わせます(ここに赤でマークしたところです)。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:274
msgid ""
"That diagonal can then in turn be used to determine the position of the "
"beams:"
msgstr "対角線はこれで枕木の場所を決めるのに使えるようになりました。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:277
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_03.png"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_03.png"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Assistants_vanishing_point_logic_03.png"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:278
msgid ""
"Because any given set of lines has a vanishing point (outside the ones flat "
"on the view-plane), there can be an infinite amount of vanishing points in a "
"linear perspective. Therefore, Krita allows you to set vanishing points "
"yourself instead of forcing you to only use a few."
msgstr ""
"どの線の組み合わせにも消失点があることから(ビューに平行なものは除いて)、線遠"
"近法には無数の数の消失点があることになります。それゆえに、限られたされたもの"
"だけでなく Krita はユーザに消失点を自由に設定することができるようになっていま"
"す。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:281
msgid "Fish Eye perspective"
msgstr "魚眼レンズ視点"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:283
msgid ""
"Fish eye perspective works much the same as the linear perspective, the big "
"difference being that in a fish-eye perspective, any parallel set of lines "
"has two vanishing points, each for one side."
msgstr ""
"魚眼パースはほとんど線遠近法のように振舞いますが、魚眼遠近であることの大きな"
"違いは、片側にそれぞれ、どの平行線の組み合わせも二つの消失点があることです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:285
msgid ""
"So, to set them up, the easiest way is one horizontal, one vertical, on the "
"same spot, and one vanishing point assistant in the middle."
msgstr ""
"設定するのに一番簡単な方法は一つを水平、もう一つを垂直の同じ場所に、最後の一"
"つは間に消失点アシストを置くことです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:288
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ".. image:: images/assistants/Fish-eye.gif"
msgid ".. image:: /images/assistants/Fish-eye.gif"
msgstr ".. image:: images/assistants/Fish-eye.gif"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:289
msgid ""
"But, you can also make one horizontal one that is just as big as the other "
"horizontal one, and put it halfway:"
msgstr ""
"しかし半分のところに水平をもう片方の水平と同じ大きさにすることでもできます:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/painting_with_assistants.rst:-1
msgid "How to use the painting assistants in Krita to draw perspectives."
msgstr "透視図を描くために Krita のお絵描きアシストを使う方法"

